US scientists used DNA testing to trace poached elephant tusks, aiding in combating the illegal ivory trade.
The seized shipment from Malawi, the largest since the 1989 ivory trade ban, represented ivory from thousands of elephants.
The situation is dire, with the potential extinction of these majestic creatures looming.
Researchers aim to convene a meeting for African elephant-holding countries to find solutions.
Kenya and Mali propose a 20-year ban on elephant tusk trade.
The need for strong enforcement is emphasized to prevent further poaching and protect these endangered animals.
